==English==
===Etymology===
from the practice of reckoning the batting average of a hitter in thousandths.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|inf=to [[bat]] [[a]] [[thousand]]|bats a thousand|batting a thousand|[[bat a thousand]] or '''[[batted a thousand]]'''}}
# {{baseball|idiom}} To reach first base on every [[at-bat]].
# {{idiom}} To achieve success at each attempt.
#: He's '''batting a thousand''' so far with the new boss.
# {{idiom}} To achieve perfection.
#: No one can '''bat a thousand''' for the whole season.

